        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer35212561" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16265346712171604861">Very nicely writting. Entertaining and hard to put down. Some portions of the book stirred my anger. Would have liked to see Eleanor AKA &quot;Nora&quot; set straight sooner with a more thorough reality check. Though Leota&apos;s two adult kids live very close to her, they have very little to do with her. She&apos;s 86ish and can no longer take care of her home, garden, and even walking to/from the store has become a chore. She&apos;s very lonely. Sitting around her home looking at all the things that need to be cleaned</span>
  <span id="freeText16265346712171604861" style="display:none">Very nicely writting. Entertaining and hard to put down. Some portions of the book stirred my anger. Would have liked to see Eleanor AKA "Nora" set straight sooner with a more thorough reality check. Though Leota's two adult kids live very close to her, they have very little to do with her. She's 86ish and can no longer take care of her home, garden, and even walking to/from the store has become a chore. She's very lonely. Sitting around her home looking at all the things that need to be cleaned (windows, yard, carpets) and no longer able to do things. Only the t.v. to keep her company. <br /><br />She decides to call the number of an add on t.v. for help. They send her a college boy, Corbin, who is writing a paper on what to do with the elderly and needed the research. These two were fun to read about. Leota was very strict with Corbin and how their relationship developed brought a smile to my face. <br /><br />The other main character in the story was Annie. Leota's estranged granddaughter and daughter of Eleanor. Eleanor held a grudge agaist Nora based on her beliefs of what transpired during her youth and had not allowed or encouraged Leota to be a part of her family. Eleanor was very controlling and manipulative. When Annie (18) rebelled and moved out, she felt the strong urge to contact her grandmother and did. They hit it off. Annie was curious about Leota because her mother repeatedly told her she they were just alike. Their relationship was such a joy. <br /><br />Leota's life changed immediately. Annie, Corbin, neighbors all started hanging out and cleaning up Leota's home and garden. Sam was courting Annie and he and his sister participated in the cleanup. <br /><br />Annie was a budding young artist and she painted walls with murals inside the home. <br /><br />What a story. How it all came together....<br /><br />I cried a lot thru the end....</span>
  <a data-text-id="16265346712171604861" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


