  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1118310552" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1118310552" />
    <a title="Mary" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5063245-mary"><img alt="Mary" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1634126629p2/5063245.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1118310552?book_show_action=true">Nov 29, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mary" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mary" href="/user/show/5063245-mary">Mary</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1118310552" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11525231678694951974">This book had been at the bottom of a stack for about 2 years. I was supposed to return it when I finished it so I was being protective of it. Well, I finally read the very moving fiction story which seemed so real like I knew the people well. I believe it is a story that my generation can understand so well, as we contrast our relationships to grandparents compared to 50 years ago. But most of all, we see people change, which is magical indeed. A young man who hasn&apos;t experienced much life gets </span>
  <span id="freeText11525231678694951974" style="display:none">This book had been at the bottom of a stack for about 2 years. I was supposed to return it when I finished it so I was being protective of it. Well, I finally read the very moving fiction story which seemed so real like I knew the people well. I believe it is a story that my generation can understand so well, as we contrast our relationships to grandparents compared to 50 years ago. But most of all, we see people change, which is magical indeed. A young man who hasn't experienced much life gets a double helping of life when he meets an incredible old lady who can keep him on his toes. He is also challenged about where he stands on life when his so-called girlfriend makes a choice without listening to him at all. But what is riveting is the developing relationship between grandmother and granddaughter when truth comes out after many years. We see how time gets away from us as the daughter in the mix tries to figure out the lies from the past that have held her captive. This is a loving, intimate story, not meant to entertain or thrill us, but put real life issues up on a big screen for us to think about. Incredible!</span>
  <a data-text-id="11525231678694951974" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

